      "content": "the code review didn't turn up anything obvious. i'm thinking about implementing a wrapper around my malloc calls to record the return address and size for every allocation, so i can build a small table in RAM to see which call sites are growing over time. do you think that overhead would be too high for a real-time system, or is there a better way to do this without crashing the timing of the control loops?",
